[815.517357, "o", "{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_57\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Implemented per assignment with TDD (added tests, confirmed failures, then fixed code).\\n\\n**Added tests**\\n- [test/finders/bidirectional.spec.js](/home/sagar/PathFinding.js-fork/test/finders/bidirectional.spec.js)\\n- [test/regressions/shared-state-and-exports.spec.js](/home/sagar/PathFinding.js-fork/test/regressions/shared-state-and-exports.spec.js)\\n\\nThese cover:\\n- BiAStar/BiBestFirst/BiBreadthFirst/BiDijkstra edge cases and diagonal-mode matrices\\n- BiBestFirst heuristic inflation + path-quality tradeoff\\n- shared reused-grid contamination (bi + non-bi), 1x1 start=end\\n- `src/PathFinding.js` export contract\\n\\n**Implementation fixes**\\n- [src/finders/AStarFinder.js](/home/sagar/PathFinding.js-fork/src/finders/AStarFinder.js): reset node search state before each run to prevent grid state leakage across repeated searches.\\n- [src/finders/BiAStarFinder.js](/home/sagar/PathFinding.js-fork/src/finders/BiAStarFinder.js): same reset "]
[815.517459, "o", "for bidirectional family (also benefits `BiBestFirst`/`BiDijkstra` since they extend this).\\n- [src/core/Util.js](/home/sagar/PathFinding.js-fork/src/core/Util.js): fixed `smoothenPath` single-point behavior (`len <= 1` returns a copy) and declared `lastValidCoord` properly.\\n\\n**Verification**\\n- Targeted new suites pass:\\n  - `npx mocha --require should test/finders/bidirectional.spec.js`\\n  - `npx mocha --require should test/regressions/shared-state-and-exports.spec.js`\\n- Full command passes:\\n  - `npx mocha --require should test/**/*.js`\\n  - Result: `93 passing` (exit code `0`).\"}}\r\n"]
